\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. C. retorta} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1}: 120 (1806). Annual; stems 10-50 cm. Lower leaves ovate to oblong-spathulate, petiolate, tuberculate; the upper cordate at base, sessile. Bracts ovate, cordate at base, violet, equalling calyx. Corolla 10-15 × 3-5 mm, curved above and constricted at throat, pale yellow, violet distally; lobes ovate, sharply recurved at apex. Nutlets blackish.{\i  Rocky places. S. & W. parts of Balkan peninsula.} Al ?Cr Gr Ju.
