\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 11.            Moltkia}              Lehm.    
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By R. Fernandes.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs or dwarf shrubs. Flowers in terminal bracteate cymes. Calyx lobed almost to the base. Corolla blue, purple or yellow, infundibuliform, without scales or annulus. Stamens exserted or included, inserted at or above the middle of the corolla; anthers sometimes apiculate but without a projecting connective at the apex and not sagittate or apiculate at the base. Style exserted; stigma small, entire or emarginate. Nutlets often solitary by abortion, ovoid and curved, usually smooth and shining, with a ventral keel, flat at base.
