\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. M. doerfleri} Wettst.,{\i  Anzeig. Akad. Wiss.} ({\i Wien}) {\b 55}: 284 (1918). Perennial herb. Stems 30-50 cm, erect, simple, appressed-setulose, produced from a thick, horizontal, sympodial rhizome. Leaves lanceolate, acute, sparsely appressed-setulose and also ciliate, the lowest imperfectly developed. Calyx c. 10 mm; lobes falling off individually before the calyx-base. Corolla 19-25 mm, gradually widened above, deep purple. Filaments 1·5-2 mm; anthers 2·5-3 mm, biapiculate, included in the tube. Nutlets c. 4 mm. •{\i  Mountains of N.E. Albania.} Al.
