\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 12.           Alkanna}           Tausch
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By S. Kozuharov.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs. Flowers in terminal, bracteate cymes. Calyx lobed almost to the base. Corolla variously coloured, with more or less cylindrical tube and infundibuliform limb, with a ring of hairs and sometimes with small invaginations in the throat. Stamens included, inserted at about the middle of the tube. Style included; stigma small, entire. Nutlets usually 2 by abortion, subreniform to obliquely ovoid and curved, granular to tuberculate, strongly stipitate.
\par

